---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Brunei Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/brunei/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Malaysia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/malaysia' },
  { title: 'Singapore for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/singapore' },
  { title: 'Thailand for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/thailand' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'bruneiFit', header: 'Brunei Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BND$660-940/mo', bruneiFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BND$770-1,100/mo', bruneiFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BND$590-845/mo', bruneiFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'BND$550-785/mo', bruneiFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Local (Takaful)', entryAge: '60', renewal: 'Varies', monthlyFrom: 'BND$200-400/mo', bruneiFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'BND$590-940', annual: 'BND$7,080-11,280' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'BND$810-1,255', annual: 'BND$9,720-15,060' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'BND$1,090-1,685', annual: 'BND$13,080-20,220' },
  { category: 'Government Healthcare', monthly: 'Free/nominal', annual: 'For residents' },
  { category: 'Private Hospital Stay', monthly: 'BND$300-800/day', annual: 'Per incident' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Brunei 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Brunei. Wealthy sultanate, free healthcare for citizens, English-speaking, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Brunei"
  subheadline="Brunei offers wealthy stability, free/subsidized healthcare, English language, no income tax, and conservative Islamic culture—a unique Southeast Asian option for select retirees."
  heroImage="/images/countries/brunei-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Brunei</h2>
  <p>
    Brunei offers oil-wealth stability, excellent infrastructure, free/subsidized healthcare for residents, English as working language, and no income tax. For those comfortable with conservative Islamic society and able to secure residence, Brunei provides unique security.
  </p>

  <p>
    Bandar Seri Begawan is the capital with main services. Kuala Belait has oil industry. Temburong is nature reserve area. The country is small (5,765 sq km) and easy to navigate. Limited entertainment but close to Malaysian Borneo for variety.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Good; free/subsidized for residents</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Malay (official); English widely used</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> BND$2,500-5,000/month (~$1,850-3,700 USD); moderate</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Tropical; hot humid year-round</li>
      <li><strong>Culture:</strong> Conservative Islamic; alcohol banned</li>
      <li><strong>Taxes:</strong> No income tax; no capital gains</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Brunei Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Brunei has good healthcare—RIPAS Hospital (government) is main facility with modern equipment. Jerudong Park Medical Centre is private option. Healthcare is free or heavily subsidized for residents. Complex cases may require Singapore or Kuala Lumpur.
  </p>

  <p>
    Government healthcare covers most needs for residents. Wait times are minimal (small population). Some specialists limited—Singapore (2-hour flight) provides backup. Oil wealth funds excellent public healthcare infrastructure.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Government Healthcare</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Brunei citizens and residents access free/subsidized government healthcare. Foreigners pay nominal fees. Quality is good for most conditions. Complex specialties require Singapore. International insurance recommended for regional options and private care.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Brunei has limited residence options:
  </p>

  <h3>Employment Pass</h3>
  <p>
    For working in Brunei. Not typical retirement route but some professionals use this.
  </p>

  <h3>Family Dependant Pass</h3>
  <p>
    For family members of Brunei citizens or workers. Various categories available.
  </p>

  <h3>Permanent Residence</h3>
  <p>
    Very difficult to obtain. Long-term residence required. Not straightforward for foreigners.
  </p>

  <h3>Tourist Entry</h3>
  <p>
    90 days visa-free for many nationalities. Not suitable for retirement but good for exploration.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Brunei:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Residents:</strong> Access government healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Practical:</strong> International coverage for regional access</li>
    <li><strong>Singapore:</strong> Include for complex conditions</li>
    <li><strong>Takaful:</strong> Islamic insurance options available locally</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Brunei</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      Government healthcare provides good base for residents. International insurance adds Singapore private access for complex conditions and travel coverage. Takaful (Islamic insurance) available for those preferring Sharia-compliant options.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Brunei, Singapore access is key supplement:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Brunei</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong Asia network, Singapore access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), worldwide</li>
    <li><strong>Government base:</strong> Excellent foundation for residents</li>
    <li><strong>Singapore backup:</strong> 2-hour flight for specialists</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare supplemental coverage for Brunei.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Brunei (BND pegged 1:1 to SGD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Government healthcare:</strong> Free/subsidized base for residents</li>
    <li><strong>High deductible:</strong> Use international for major only</li>
    <li><strong>Singapore network:</strong> Use designated hospitals</li>
    <li><strong>Regional plans:</strong> Southeast Asia focused options</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Oil Industry Retiree, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $4,500/month pension. Post-career residence. BSB.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Government healthcare + Cigna Global supplemental.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BND$700/month supplement. Industry connection; dual coverage.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: British Muslim Convert, 70</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £3,000/month pension. Family connection. Conservative lifestyle preferred.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Government healthcare + BUPA Global for travel.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BND$900/month. Islamic environment; global backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Singaporean Spouse, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> S$3,500/month income. Brunei citizen spouse. Commuting lifestyle.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Government access + Allianz Care for Singapore treatment.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~BND$650/month. Cross-border ease; dual access.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Can foreigners retire to Brunei?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Difficult—no retirement visa. Residence requires employment, family connection, or special circumstances. Permanent residence very hard to obtain. Not a straightforward retirement destination for most foreigners.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is alcohol really banned?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Yes—sale and public consumption of alcohol is banned. Non-Muslims can import limited quantities for private consumption. No bars, clubs, or alcohol sales. This is major lifestyle consideration for many expats.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Brunei expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderate—cheaper than Singapore, similar to Malaysia. Imported goods are costly. Fuel and utilities are subsidized. Healthcare is free/cheap. Overall moderate cost; not budget destination but not extreme.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What is there to do in Brunei?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Limited entertainment—no nightlife, no alcohol. Nature activities, mosques, rainforest. Close to Malaysian Borneo for variety. Quiet lifestyle. Not for those seeking excitement. Suits those wanting peaceful, conservative environment.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Brunei coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Brunei authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
